\begin_layout Subsection
Dataset
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We follow the algorithm of DeTone et al.
 for dataset generation as well as the parameters used.
 That is, all images are scaled to 320x240 pixels and are converted to grayscale.
 128x128 pixel patches are used, and the corner offset is sampled from a
 uniform distribution of [-32, 32] pixels.
 We use images from the COCO 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "lin2014microsoft"

\end_inset

 2017 
\shape italic
test
\shape default
 and 
\shape italic
val
\shape default
 datasets to generate 12 samples per image, resulting in a pool of around
 550,000 samples.
 We use 500,000 samples for training and set aside the remaining 50,000
 samples for both validation and testing.
\end_layout

